  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_0' aria-label=\" Directorate of Enforcement versus Subhash Sharma pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('0','2025','2025_1_1409_1412','2025INSC141'); ><font size='4'> <strong>DIRECTORATE OF ENFORCEMENT<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>SUBHASH SHARMA </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 1 S.C.R. 1409</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 141</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002642025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : ABHAY S. OKA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, UJJAL BHUYAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court was justified in holding that the respondent's arrest was illegal and thus, granting him bail for an offence under Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002. Headnotes&dagger; Bail &ndash; Prevention of Money Laundering Act, 2002 &ndash; ss.45, 65 Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 &ndash; s.57 &ndash; Arrest vitiated if fundamental rights of the accused u/Arts.21 and 22 were violated &ndash; On facts, arrest of the respondent, if was illegal: Held: Yes &ndash; Respondent was not produced before the Magistrate within 24 hours from his<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 21-01-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 310/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Dismissed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('0','2025','2025_1_1409_1412','2025INSC141','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-auto'><a href='#'